            <title>[BEAM-8959] Boolean pipeline options which default to true cannot be set to false</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-8959</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the included argument parser, any boolean pipeline options which default to true cannot be set to false, e.g. &lt;tt&gt;--enable_metrics=false&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;error: argument --enable_metrics: ignored explicit argument &apos;false&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
